oai_dc:dc.dc:title: General James Winchester portrait
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Portrait of General James Winchester (1752-1826). Portrait from waist up. He wears a dark coat and white collar and necktie. He has a paper in his hand. Possibly white hair. Narrative on reverse.
Co-Founder of Memphis, Tennessee; Trustee of Davidson County. Winchester was a veteran of the Revolutionary War and served as a general in the War of 1812.
